UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''As Waterspeaker, I performed many rituals. There is one, though, that I have never performed - to purify mental corruption.\\n\\nIt is an ancient ritual, one which we have not needed since days of legend, when Shaohao walked Pandaria.\\n\\nI fear we need it now...''' WHERE `ID`=61162;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''While I would love to purify all of my corrupted bretheren, I cannot allow those of us who have not fallen to corruption to go leaderless.\\n\\nWe must stop the spread of this vile influence, and then I will lead those of us who remain pure to freedom.''' WHERE `ID`=61167;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''Every Shado-Pan makes three eternal oaths:\\n\\nTo defend this land, to protect its people, and to train their pupil.\\n\\nWhen a Shado-Pan dies, they must be released from these bonds.''' WHERE `ID`=61493;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''Ah, it was a difficult battle. So sad to have lost friends.\\n\\nThough, I am glad I had them build the battlefield refreshment device.\\n\\nWithout it, and without the power of my stout brew, who knows how many more would have been lost...''' WHERE `ID`=61494;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='''We could use a $c. Glad to see my husband sent you along.\\n\\nI''''m a scout, not much for face-to-face combat. And Lao-chen here... well, normally he''''s a fighter, but he''''s still exhausted from the last battle.\\n\\nAnd, he''''s too busy cooking up some scheme.''' WHERE `ID`=61501;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='''Lin is upset - Zhiya was his good friend and we lost him in the battle. \\n\\nI don''''t want Lin to do something thoughtless. I don''''t know what I''''d do if I lost him...''' WHERE `ID`=61657;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''Zhiyao dead. Shiya dead. Liu dead.\\n\\nSuna councils me to calm, but honor demands otherwise.\\n\\nTaran Zhu sits safe in the monastery while we defend the pass alone? Why shut us out? Why not send reinforcements?\\n\\nThese questions trouble me.''' WHERE `ID`=61658;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''At first, my deference and respect for Taran Zhu prohibited me from questioning his decision to close the monastery to outsiders.\\n\\nThen, when the yaungol first attacked, my focus on the battle at hand prevented me from leaving the front lines to question his inability to send reinforcements.\\n\\nNow, three Shado-Pan lie dead, one is captured, and my patience is beyond worn thin - it is gone. I plan to go to the monastery and demand an audience with Taran Zhu.''' WHERE `ID`=61674;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='''Well, you really sent them flying. I could hear their... bleating from here. \\n\\nBleating? Is that what you call the sound of a yaungol flying off a wall?''' WHERE `ID`=61691;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='''Wow. I could hear the explosions from up on the wall.\\n\\nI guess not ALL of Lao-Chen''''s ideas are terrible.''' WHERE `ID`=61692;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''Another attack?!\\n\\nThese yaungol will not relent until we push them back into Townlong. Or, even better, into the sea.''' WHERE `ID`=61696;
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='''After all this... our brothers and sisters passing, Lin captured by yaungol, my beer gone, I think it''''s time to move along.\\n\\nPerhaps I''''ll take the fight to the mantid...''' WHERE `ID`=61700;
